     A few items of interest...

                        ==============================

     There are times when it is actually amusing to watch what happens
     in FidoNet, especially when certain individuals make attempts to
     prove a point, and don't realize what is in store for them.

     Doc Logger appears, again, having made an erroneous assumption in
     his previous column...it makes no difference and actually points out
     precisely the point I was indeed trying to make...and to answer his
     unspoken question, it takes me about seven hours to read the book.
     Doc did good...he just hasn't realized why yet.

                        ==============================

     And the "scorched earth" policy seems to be moving to a quick and
     earnest conclusion...

     John Souvestre has apparently decided to go for an "endgame" in
     making a direct challenge to the Z1EC, Bob Kohl, by making several
     accusations, including the claim that the Editor of the FidoNews
     has refused to post election results as submitted.

     Likewise, John has decided to join in the furor over my "true
     identity", and make claims that I have committed "voter fraud".

     As well, allegations of 'bribery' and 'payoffs' have been made.

     A pity that Mr. Souvestre is about to become the very foolish
     looking person that he has long been accused of being...and by his
     very own hand.

     I would, again, point out to John that the FidoNews publishes what
     is submitted to it...and the only "editing" done is to meet the
     margin requirements (which occasionally slip by...sorry, Michele!).

     As to the rest...

     Keep watching, everyone...this should prove to be highly
     entertaining.

                        ==============================

     This line with the mention of "Ward Dossche" is included to meet the
     alleged 'all-consuming devotion of the FidoNews Editorial' with Ward.
     As it is, Ward has not submitted his "Doomsday Countdown" for the
     last few weeks and, at his specific request, I am not publishing any
     copy of it without his permission.

                        ==============================
     FIDONEWS 15-19               Page 2                   11 May 1998


     However, to that end, it appears from tossing the nodediff here each
     week that it may indeed be time to look at the long-quelled and oft
     suppressed (or so several have said) requests from various sysops to
     establish a new Zone in FidoNet...Zone 7.

     The advantages are obvious...it significantly lessens the chances
     of tie votes in the ZCC; it balances the Zones and gives more direct
     representation to the sysops involved; and it reduces the chances of
     Regional Coordinators being drowned out when they wish to address
     issues of their areas.

     The downside of it is, of course, that the current "majority" in the
     confines of Zone 2 would likely be reduced to a comparable level
     with all other Zones, but what's more important...maintaining a
     majority, or enhancing and enabling representation closer to the real
     population?

     As well, with the advent of BinkD and ARGUS, it may be that the
     future center of new developments in FidoNet is shifting yet once
     again...

     An issue to consider for the ZCC, no doubt...along with another.

                        ==============================

     Yet another FTSC member has resigned from the group, citing some
     personal reasons.

     I believe this means we have lost a total of three FTSC members, but
     I can't be certain since I've seemingly been denied access to the
     FTSC echoes overall, even though I was elected to that body.

     As a member of FTSC, I've not been able to gain access to the FTSC
     Working Group echoes since these were established, and only five
     messages have passed through the main FTSC echo since these echoes
     were established.

     I'm certain that this is *merely* an oversight, but my queries as
     to where to get a feed from have been met with stony silence and
     a 'humorous' comment that I have been added to the SEEN-BY of every
     member's posts.

     Since I've received no real responses to my queries, I suppose that
     posting this here instead may garner a few more serious responses,
     no?

     Or, at the least, present a case for the ZCC to decide on the merits
     and usefulness of the newest incarnation of the FTSC.

     Communication doesn't work if it is only one way...

                        ==============================

     Next week, I will attempt to carry out something that hasn't been
     seen in the FidoNews in quite some time...a personal interview with
     another member of FidoNet in a face-to-face meeting.
     FIDONEWS 15-19               Page 3                   11 May 1998


     Let's see if we can meet before I say who and where...

                        ==============================

     And that's it...a few items of interest to consider, one and all.

