     Remembering Frank Ellermann of 2:240/5815
     by Wulf Krueger, 2:2437/209

     FIDONEWS 15-19               Page 6                   11 May 1998


     Only a few of you out there will have noticed what has happened
     in Nodelist 114. One of us has finally dropped from the Nodelist
     after having been down for around 5 months. Why do I mention this
     fact? Many nodes are leaving today daily.

     Frank Ellermann, formerly known as 2:240/5815, was a very special
     person. He had excellent skills in FidoNet techniques; IMHO he
     was one of the most brilliant among us. He has been actively
     developing FSCs (now known as FSPs) and he wrote small piece of
     FTN software himself. But there was much more to him..

     Frank was not only an excellent technician but he was an out-
     standing personality. He was a very kind and gentle person. We
     all know our common ways in FidoNet today - bashing and throwing
     dirt at each other. I have never seen him writing such mails.
     Frank always tried to see the "bright side of life" and the
     bright side of every single person - even if it was someone he
     did not like. Even when he was attacked himself he never chose
     to flame back, he took it with much humour. For this behaviour
     he was widely respected by those who knew him. Even those who
     critisized him respected him as a person.

     Frank wrote long mails (he was famous for that, too,
     Frank "Ellenlang" ;) ) about FTN, about democratic principles in
     FidoNet and (sometimes) about life in general.
     He was one of the authors of the local policy of R2:24, the so-
     called RegPol24 which IMHO helped us very much to establish
     democratic principles in R2:24. He has given much advice to
     the current ZC2, Ward Dossche, myself and many others - to anyone
     who asked him.

     Frank always seemed to be full of joy though he was not the kind
     of person to show his personal feelings to anyone. I knew him
     for several years and learned to interpret his words quite well,
     we became very good friends in fact. Indeed, I consider him
     having once saved my life.

     Frank joined FidoNet late in 1994 and became a node in 1995.
     Now Frank has completely disappeared and it really hurts me and
     makes me feel bad. When Frank had to go down in the middle of
     Decembre 1997 we both hoped that he would come up again. I spoke
     to him on the 15th of January this year and as always he sounded
     very good. :-)
     Since that day I have lost any contact. Frank has no telephone
     anymore and he doesn't answer my letters. When I tried to visit
     him he did not answer the door bell. I hope and I suppose he is
     physically well but having lost him as a fellow node and, which
     is much harder for me, as a good friend is very sad but it's his
     decision.

     Concerning his FSCs I ask Odinn Sorensen, chairman of the new
     FTSC, to take Frank's submission as *public domain*. This is
     what Frank wanted if his node was removed from the Nodelist to
     make sure that they could be improved by others who take up his
     good work and I want this to come true to honour him.

     FIDONEWS 15-19               Page 7                   11 May 1998


     I ask all you others out there, those of you how knew him, those
     of you who have read his name in FTSC_PUBLIC or elsewhere and all
     others, to remember him, to take up where he had to stop, to try
     to take him as an example of how to communicate with others.
     FidoNet could be much more human and much more fun then.

     At least I will always remember him and I wish him the best of
     luck.

     If you should, by any means, get to read this, Frank, I hope you
     will remember my words in one of our last netmails.
     I miss you.

     Wulf Krueger of 2:2437/209

